Dear Madam or Sir,
 
I'm a postgraduate student from Warwick Manufacturing Group (United Kingdom). I'm currently conducting a research for my Master’s dissertation “Developing a successful business model for a medical tourism website MedEGate.com”. I will truly appreciate if you could spend some time answering questions of an online survey. Your responses are important in enabling me to obtain as full an understanding as possible of this topical issue. 

The online survey will consist of 19 questions and wont take much of your time. If you are unsure about the answer simply skip the question.

In order to complete the survey please click on the link below:

http://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/sci/wmg/project/studentsurvey/veranikasianko/surveyformedegate

The purpose of this study is to to obtain as full an understanding as possible about medical tourism. This method of obtaining information is a part of a research project to find out the most effective type of business model  for medical tourism. The general idea of medical tourism website MedEGate.com is to provide worldwide information on hospitals, insurance companies, clinics, sanatoriums and spa resorts for people in search of medical and health treatment. The website will serve as a platform, which will bringing together prospective patients with healthcare providers and assisting the first in planning their medical travel. The website is going to use generalized approach providing multiple services over a wide range of medical specialties.

The information you provide will be treated in the strictest confidence. You will notice that you are not asked to include your name and address anywhere on the questionnaire.
 
The findings from your questionnaire and others will be used as the main data set for my dissertation for my degree course in Innovation and Entrepreneurship at the University of Warwick.
 
If you have any queries or would like further information, please feel free to contact me.

Many thanks!

Veronika Sianko
Mob (Uk): 07539344879
Email: veranika.sianko@warwick.ac.uk
             Veronika.sianko@gmail.com
